{
  "texts": [
    "Retrieved tweetsOverall, we retrieved 2.69 • 10 7 tweets belonging to 348 stories.",
    "On average, we collected 7.72 • 10 4 tweets per story (median: 9.98 • 10 4, see Fig. 3g).",
    "It is, however, important to note that we had to perform tweet sampling for 235 ( 67.53%) stories, as the respective number of matching tweets exceeded the threshold of 10 5.",
    "The distribution of the num- ber of matching tweets (see Fig. 3f) was highly right-skewed, making a log 10 -transfor- mation necessary.",
    "This pattern of (extremely) skewed distributions is very common for social data (see, e.g., [23]) and may partially reflect the 'viral' nature of social media or biases introduced by algorithms used by the social networking services [7]."
  ]
}